<plot>Pascal Robitaille's astonishing HIVERNAM mixes fictional, personal, and documentary material that is characterized with a poetically sensitive approach to black and white, light and texture. For Robitaille, reality is the sum of the physical and the spiritual, and cinema is where the two can meet. The film features well-known figures from the french canadian cinema and television, such as Joël Drapeau-Dalpé, Xavier Morin-Lefort, Frédéric Lemay and Noémie Yelle.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?242012</url></doc>
